			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				And on a lighter note....<BR>
<BR>
one of us mentioned &quot;Singing is an incredible taunt&quot;<BR>
well, I have to majorly agree.  it is a massive taunt. warriors of up to 3 levels higher than you WILL have problems pulling mobs off you with taunt.  <BR>
Q. Why does this happen?<BR>
<BR>
A. It happens because of how the mob peices together its agro-list. our songs make us look to them like casters.. and dangerous ones that their spells affect the whole group...  its strateigicly sound to try to kill us first.<BR>
<BR>
Many young bards have switched to other classes because of this...  But is it a weakness or just a strength most yet do not understand.<BR>
<BR>
my answer is &quot;Strength&quot; because I've used it to my groups advantage many times.<BR>
<BR>
Example #1<BR>
<BR>
Once while hunting orcs in oasis, the person in the group pulled far to many orcs... they would have ripped thru all of us FAST... but what did I do?  I flicked on Chords of dissonance for a couple of ticks (i took the lead on the majority of the orcs Agro-Lists) Then i flicked out my drums and switched on selo's and ran laps of the lake.  while I was &quot;entertaining&quot; most of the orcs, my group finnished off the few that remained and healed up... after that I had them pick the orcs off me one by one.<BR>
<BR>
Example #2<BR>
I've used it to Power Level a young bard once...<BR>
I brought the young bard (lev 9) out to WC after his group at orc 1 was slaughtered by shin ree.<BR>
I brought him out twards the inn near the shadowed man camp...  I pulled Kodiaks, Young Kodiaks etc back to him... using a quick smack from my sword initialy and then chain singing &quot;Selo's Constaint Chain&quot; I kept myself on the top of the agro list while the young bard, who would have normaly been slaughtered by a full grown kodiak, cut it down to size.<BR>
<BR>
so in conclusion, yes it is a difficult trait to deal with. But if you discover its uses, it becomes another tool in our masive &quot;Bag O' Tricks&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Keep safe out there, young ones
