			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Oorscaat? Just how gullible are you? A &quot;bard&quot; come to your page and asked you here? Wake up. It was probably just another idiot necro trying to get something started. Duuuuuuhhhh. I'm glad your trying a bard, but c'mon, don't be so dense. And don't expect everyone else to be that dense either. You came here for one reason, not because you were answering some &quot;challenge&quot;, but because you had nothing better to do than any of the rest of these children (not just necros, but anyone who goes to other pages just to flame) who came here to start something.<BR>
<BR>
But since we're all here, let's get something straight. Yes, Necros are tough. I wouldn't take anything away from them. Their ability to solo is awesome. BUT. They are not All-powerfull. They aren't even in the top 3 on PvP servers. Guess who is........ummm...That's right!! A bard. I can't speak for all bards, but I've never been beaten by a Necro. Only twice did one even come close. <BR>
<BR>
Why do you think so many necros come to this page to flame, huh? Could it be because they get their ass kicked so much in EQ that they have to come to everlore.com and go to the bards page and call them names.....hmmmmm, you know, I think that about nails it.<BR>
<BR>
Grow up kiddies. Use the pages for what they are meant for. Go back to your own page and talk about how you feared some blue conning mob and let your pet cut it down from behind.<BR>
<BR>
But since your here, you might as well listen to some of the finer aspects of being a bard. We can melee, dual wield, run faster than SoW, AoE Fear, Charm, Mez, Snare, Track, Sense Traps, Disarm Traps, Pick Locks, Safe Fall, Sneak, Hide, Levitate (better actually), DoT, DD, Parry, Reposte, wear heavy armor, use most weapons, breath under water, Shadow Step, Cancel Magic, Buff, Regenerte Health, Regenerate Mana, Regenerate Stamina, and KICK your NECRO A$$.<BR>
<BR>
In groups, we are almost always welcome. For we can fill the role of most other character types the group may not have present. We may not be as good at a certain thing that another class is, but we can sure take up the slack. And that very diversity is what makes us such a great class, cause alone, I can go just about anywhere or do just about anything cause I got some skill or song for just about any situation. If only a bard could port....<BR>
 <BR>
Want to test the theory? I'm on Zebuxoruk server. Send me a tell. We'll dual in my favorite zone, EC. Why? Cause there are both Newbies and High Level PC's to witness it.<BR>
<BR>
Or better yet, play a bard and enjoy. Other wise, keep playing with your pets and paying or begging everyone else to Buff, SoW, Clarity, and Port your sorry asses.<BR>
<BR>
Personally, if I wanted to depend on a Pet, I'd play a Magician. They definately kick the $hit outta Necros on PvP servers, and they too rank in the top 3. I've just started one myself. He's only 4th level now, but I'm sure he'll be busted Necro ass soon enough.<BR>
<BR>
To all my fellow skalds out there, I just want to say Hi, and keep on rockin my friends. Norrath would be a boring place without us.<BR>
<BR>
Rhymel Sylverblade &lt;Eques de Aterum Rosa&gt;<BR>
Bard of the Realms<BR>
The Poet Priest of Nothing
				</font>
			</td>

